OL,3,C'I don't want to die in hospital' -
OL,4,CFunding crisis threatens end-of-life
OL,5,Ccare
OL,7,FA 51-year-old man in Sussex fears he
OL,8,Fwill have to die in hospital if his
OL,9,Flocal hospice can't offer him a bed
OL,10,Fbecause of a lack of funding.
OL,12,FMarc Valentine was diagnosed with a
OL,13,Frare progressive cancer five years
OL,14,Fago. Since then, staff at Martlets
OL,15,FHospice in Hove have become like
OL,16,Ffamily to him.
OL,18,FBut the hospice says increased costs
OL,19,Fand a lack of financial support from
OL,20,Fthe government mean it might have to
OL,21,Freduce its services.
